According to the calculations, the band gap energies (Eg
                        ) of CM-2 and MIL-53(Fe)-NO2 were 1.93 and 1.97 eV (Fig. S6B), demonstrating the band gap energy decreased after doping CDs. The conduction bands (Ecb
                        ) of CM-2 and MIL-53(Fe)-NO2 were investigated by the Mott-Schottky analysis, which were −0.25 and −0.21 eV (Fig. S6C). The fact of CM-2 showing a smaller slope indicated CM-2 had a larger concentration of electron donors (Wang et al., 2021). The electron transfer rates were assessed using the electrochemical impedance spectroscopy (Fig. 3F), and the small semicircle diameter reflected a rapid charge transfer.
